headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard scored 30 points, Paul George had 21 and Norman Powell added 19 off the bench to give the Los Angeles Clippers a 112-98 win over the Dallas Mavericks on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Leonard, George lead Clippers past Mavericks, 112-98

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Miami Heat

headlines.description: — It was Kids Day in Miami, so it made sense that the youngest Heat starter would lead the way.
headlines.shortLinkText: Herro scores 26, Heat come from 16 down, top Pelicans 100-96

events.name: New York Knicks at Toronto Raptors

headlines.description: — Fred VanVleet scored 28 points, Gary Trent Jr. had 24 before fouling out and the Toronto Raptors snapped a three-game losing streak by beating the New York Knicks 125-116 Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: VanVleet scores 28, Raptors hand Knicks 4th straight loss

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander banked in a decisive 8-foot jumper with 9.2 seconds remaining and finished with 34 points as the Oklahoma City Thunder snapped Denver’s league-leading nine-game win streak and beat the Nuggets 101-99 Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander hits winner, lifts Thunder past Nuggets

headlines.description: — Chris Paul played so well in his return from a hip injury that it appeared the Phoenix Suns would have a surprise snoozer on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Paul returns, Suns hold on for 112-110 win over Grizzlies

events.name: Brooklyn Nets at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Royce O'Neale walked gingerly onto the podium with an ice bag around each knee and reiterated the soaring confidence level among the Brooklyn Nets even with star Kevin Durant on the sidelines nursing a knee injury.
headlines.shortLinkText: O'Neale's late 3-pointer lifts Nets past Warriors 120-116

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — LeBron James said the Lakers had a choice when trailing by 25 points at halftime against the Trail Blazers.
headlines.shortLinkText: James scores 37, Lakers rally past Trail Blazers 121-112
